  "prompt": "What does it mean if you are vomiting white foam?",
  "response": "Vomiting white foam can be caused by several conditions:\n\n1. Common causes:\n- Empty stomach\n- Acid reflux\n- Excessive alcohol consumption\n- Morning sickness\n- Indigestion\n\n2. Potential serious medical conditions:\n- Gastritis\n- Kidney disease\n- Pancreatitis\n- Kennel cough (in dogs)\n- Bloat\n- Intestinal blockage\n\n3. Additional symptoms to watch for:\n- Persistent vomiting\n- Fever\n- Abdominal pain\n- Dehydration\n- Weight loss\n\n4. When to seek medical attention:\n- Vomiting for more than 24 hours\n- Blood in vomit\n- Severe abdominal pain\n- Signs of dehydration\n- High fever\n- Inability to keep fluids down\n\n5. Potential treatments:\n- Rest\n- Hydration\n- Bland diet\n- Over-the-counter medications\n- Medical intervention if symptoms persist\n\nIf you're experiencing persistent white foam vomiting or have additional concerning symptoms, it's best to consult a healthcare professional for proper diagnosis and treatment.",
